cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about improving neural machine translation (NMT) by using both labeled (parallel corpora) and unlabeled (monolingual corpora) data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which includes papers on natural language processing and machine translation. The paper also proposes a novel approach using autoencoders, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves training NMT models, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions experiments on a Chinese-English dataset, which could potentially fall under computer vision (cs.CV) if the dataset includes images or neural networks (cs.NE) if the experiments involve training deep learning models.
